AWKA – Vincent Okpala, the Anambra State Commissioner for Health, has inaugurated a Primary Health Centre built by Umudioka Community in Awka South Local Government Area of the state. The commissioner used the opportunity to urge stakeholders and communities to emulate the development effort of Umudioka Community. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Okpala emphasised that the state government’s interest was to ensure that the six basic building blocks of healthcare were achieved, one of which was a good healthcare delivery service to the people. According to him, it has been government intention for stakeholders and communities to partner with government in providing quality healthcare centres across the state and that the state government was committed to providing enabling environment for the partnership. He said government was satisfied with the quality of facilities it inaugurated at the healthcare centre and that it would ensure adequate personnel were deployed to the facility.